'''Lega Autonomia Lombarda''' (''Lombard Autonomy League'', LAL), also known as '''Lega per l'Autonomia Lombarda''' (''League for the Lombard Autonomy'')<ref name="parlamento">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlamento.it/japp/bgt/showdoc/frame.jsp?tipodoc=Resaula&leg=14&id=00008322&part=doc_dc-ressten_rs-ddltit_rdddddl608dplrdds:1-trattazione_ddvf-intervento_depaoli&parse=no |title=Legislatura 14ª - Aula - Resoconto stenografico della seduta n. 046 del 28/09/2001 |publisher=parlamento.it|accessdate=2015-02-10}}</ref><ref name="senato">{{cite web|url=http://www.senato.it/japp/bgt/showdoc/frame.jsp?tipodoc=Resaula&leg=14&id=00136796&part=doc_dc-ressten_rs-ddltit_sddeacmdddl3344pdaplse-intervento_depaolimistolal&parse=no |title=Legislatura 14ª - Aula - Resoconto stenografico della seduta n. 792 del 04/05/2005 |publisher=senato.it|accessdate=2015-02-10}}</ref> and whose extended name was '''Lega per l'Autonomia–Alleanza Lombarda–Lega Pensionati''' (''League for Autonomy–Lombard Alliance–Pensioners League''), was a [[left wing politics|left-wing]] [[Regionalism (politics)|regionalist]] [[list of political parties in Italy|political party in Italy]], based in [[Lombardy]].

==History==
The party was formed in the run-up of the [[Italian Senate election in Lombardy, 1996|1996 general election]] by the merger of [[Autonomy Lombard Alliance]] and [[Lega Alpina Lumbarda]]. The former was a 1989 split from [[Lega Lombarda]]–[[Lega Nord]] led by [[Angela Bossi]] and [[Pierangelo Brivio]] (wife and husband, sister and brother-in-law to [[Umberto Bossi]] respectively), while the latter was the political vehicle of [[Elidio De Paoli]], who had been elected in the [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate]] both in [[1992 Italian general election|1992]] and [[1994 Italian general election|1994]].

In the 1996 election the LAL obtained 1.9% of the vote in Lombardy and none of its candidates was elected.<ref name="interno">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=21/04/1996&tpa=I&tpe=R&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=3&levsut1=1&ne1=3&es0=S&es1=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Senato del 21 Aprile 1996|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

After a row between De Paoli and the couple Bossi-Brivio, the party was disbanded until 2001, when De Paoli re-organized it from scratch.

In the [[Italian Senate election in Lombardy, 2001|2001 general election]] the party won 5.4% for the Senate in Lombardy<ref name="interno2">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=13/05/2001&tpa=I&tpe=R&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=3&levsut1=1&ne1=3&es0=S&es1=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Senato del 13 Maggio 2001|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> and 0.9% nationally,<ref name="interno3">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=13/05/2001&tpa=I&tpe=A&lev0=0&levsut0=0&es0=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Senato del 13 Maggio 2001|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> as some disgruntled voters of Lega Nord and many unintended voters gave their vote to the LAL. De Paoli was elected senator with proportional representation, after he had won 11.5% in the constituency of [[Albino, Italy|Albino]]. There he stole many votes from [[Roberto Calderoli]], deputy for Albino since 1994 and most voted ''leghista'' in [[1996 Italian general election|1996]] (51.9%<ref name="interno4">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=C&dtel=21/04/1996&tpa=I&tpe=L&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=4&levsut1=1&lev2=20&levsut2=2&ne1=4&ne2=420&es0=S&es1=S&es2=S&ms=S&unipro=uni|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Camera del 21 Aprile 1996|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>), who was elected with a mere 44.2%.<ref name="interno5">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=13/05/2001&tpa=I&tpe=L&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=3&levsut1=1&lev2=32&levsut2=2&ne1=3&ne2=332&es0=S&es1=S&es2=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Senato del 13 Maggio 2001|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

In the [[Italian general election, 2006 (Lombardy)|2006 general election]] the party was affiliated to [[The Union (political coalition)|The Union]], the centre-left coalition led by [[Romano Prodi]], and its 0.1% (1.6% in Lombardy)<ref name="interno6">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=C&dtel=09/04/2006&tpa=I&tpe=A&lev0=0&levsut0=0&es0=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Camera del 9 Aprile 2006|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> was decisive for the coalition's victory over the centre-right [[House of Freedoms]] coalition.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Razza padana|author1=Signore, A.|author2=Trocino, A.|date=2010|publisher=Bureau|isbn=9788858602638|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ctn7SgNSF_QC|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref> Subsequently De Paoli was appointed undersecretary in [[Prodi II Cabinet]].<ref name="governo">{{cite web|url=http://governo.it/Governo/Governi/prodi2.html|title=Governo Italiano - I Ministri del governo Prodi|publisher=governo.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

In the [[Italian general election, 2008 (Lombardy)|2008 general election]] the LAL won a mere 0.8% for the Senate in Lombardy.<ref name="interno7">{{cite web|url=http://elezionistorico.interno.it/index.php?tpel=S&dtel=13/04/2008&tpa=I&tpe=R&lev0=0&levsut0=0&lev1=3&levsut1=1&ne1=3&es0=S&es1=S&ms=S|title=::: Ministero dell'Interno ::: Archivio Storico delle Elezioni - Senato del 13 Aprile 2008|publisher=elezionistorico.interno.it|accessdate=2014-10-31}}</ref>

In 2009 the Ministry of the Interior assigned the party's symbol to [[Matteo Brivio]], son of Angela Bossi and Pierangelo Brivio. Consequently, De Paoli returned to use Lega Alpina Lumbarda's symbol, with disappointing results. Since 2008 the LAL did not participate in any major electoral competition and M. Brivio joined [[Lega Nord]].<ref name="repubblica">{{cite web|url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2011/10/31/news/i-bossi-questione-di-famiglia-1.36987 |title=I Bossi, questione di famiglia|publisher=espresso.repubblica.it|accessdate=2015-02-10}}</ref>

